      "title": "New helper name hides the deferred callback contract",
      "why": "`RestoreAFileWithErr` reads like an eager restore operation, but the helper actually stages files, invokes `onBatch`, and returns a follow-up callback that the caller must execute later to finish the flow.",
      "scope": "br/pkg/restore/snap_client/pitr_collector_test.go:45 and the `TestConcurrency` call site at line 319",
      "anchor": {
        "path": "br/pkg/restore/snap_client/pitr_collector_test.go",
        "line": 45,
        "side": "RIGHT"
      },
      "risk_if_unchanged": "Future test changes can easily treat this as a complete restore step and forget the required callback phase, which makes the helper harder to use correctly without reopening the implementation.",
      "evidence": "The new method name only signals an added `error` return, while its actual contract is two-stage: `cb, err := coll.RestoreAFileWithErr(batch)` at line 319 and the real completion happens later in a separate `cb()` loop.",
      "change_request": "Prefer a name that exposes the deferred-work contract; current name is confusing. For example, rename this helper to something that signals it prepares or returns a completion callback rather than performing the full restore immediately."
    }
  ]
}
